data-triple-N3.o: "Zarch (also known under its ported name of Virus) is a computer game written by David Braben (better known as the co-author of Elite) in three months in 1987, for the release of the Acorn Archimedes computer. Zarch started off as a demo called Lander which was bundled with almost all releases of the Acorn Archimedes. Zarch was released as Virus and in 1988 ported to the Atari ST, Commodore Amiga, and IBM PC."@en
